A gang of about 30 armed men raided a local bar at Mukalwa shopping center in Matungulu sub-county on Saturday night where they attacked and seriously injured revellers, leaving one person dead.  Another victim is fighting for his life at Kangundo level 4 hospital after sustaining serious injuries inflicted by the assailants who stormed the village liquor joint at night.  According to senior assistant chief of Sengani sub-location, Catherine Mwikali, the gang leader, who is an ex-convict at Kamiti maximum security prison, is among five suspects who were rounded up and arrested by police in Tala following the early morning operation.    The suspects were booked in Tala police station through OB number 5/30/5/2021. The motive of the attack was not immediately established.  Ruai, Mathare squatters seek to seize KBC land  Cholera sickens more than 20 in Matungulu  Wiper's Mule retains Matungulu parliamentary seat   Former MP to go head-to-head with rivals for Matungulu seat The chief said the suspects will be processed for criminal charges once police complete the investigation.  The deceased's body was removed to Kangundo hospital mortuary.  Take a quick survey and help us improve our website!  Jubilee administration under fire as CORD luminaries accuse tribalism and corruption  Wakazi wa Matungulu wanaishi kwa hofu, wakilalamikia chimbo linalohatarisha maisha yao  Kinara wa Wiper Kalonzo Musyoka aongoza mkutano Matungulu By Erastus Mulwa | 1 day ago By Peterson Githaiga | 2 days ago By Philip Muasya | 2 days ago By Erastus Mulwa | 2 days ago Grab a copy of the latest Standard for only 10 shillings & access the last 10 editions for free